It is believed that the pedestrian failed to notice oncoming traffic when he was crossing the road. JOHANNESBURG - A man was killed after being knocked over by a car on the N14 in Diepsloot, north of Johannesburg yesterday.It is believed that the pedestrian failed to notice oncoming traffic when he was crossing the road. Authorities are still investigating the case.ER24's Russel Meiring: &quot;On arrival, paramedics found a light motor vehicle parked in the emergency lane of the highway while the body of the man was found some distance off to the side of the road. The ER24 paramedics immediately assessed the man and found that he had sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life.&quot;(Edited by Zunaid Ismael)